hits.description_en:
This module introduces advanced notions regarding the modeling and control of motion of an orbiting space system made of multiple connected bodies. A paradigmatic example of these systems is an orbiting spacecraft with one or multiple on-board robotic manipulators. 
The class lectures cover theoretical, analytical and algorithmic elements, and utilizes slide presentations, development at the whiteboards, and discussions.  
The class exercises consist of the following main elements:
-Repetition and discussion of key concepts from the lectures;
-Solving of analytical problems;
-Solving of numerical problems and exercises with a calculator;

